solution:
We first draw a diagram: [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, F;
A = (0, 4);
B = (-3, 0);
C = (7, 0);
D = 0.5 * B + 0.5 * C;
E = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * C;
F = 0.4 * A + 0.6 * D;
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--E);
draw(A--D);
label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, NW);
label("$C$", C, NE);
label("$D$", D, SE);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, SW);
[/asy] From the diagram, we can see that $\triangle EFC$ and $\triangle EFB$ have the same height, and that the base of $\triangle EFC$ is half the base of $\triangle EFB.$  This means that the area of $\triangle EFC$ is half the area of $\triangle EFB.$

Similarly, $\triangle DFC$ and $\triangle DFB$ have the same height, and the base of $\triangle DFC$ is half the base of $\triangle DFB.$  This means that the area of $\triangle DFC$ is half the area of $\triangle DFB.$

Since $[FDE] = 4,$ the area of $\triangle DFB$ is $4 + 4 = 8.$  Then the area of $\triangle EFB$ is $16,$ and the area of $\triangle EFC$ is 8, so the area of $\triangle EBC$ is $16 + 8 = 24.$  Then the area of triangle $ABC$ is $48.$

[asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, F;
A = (0, 4);
B = (-3, 0);
C = (7, 0);
D = 0.5 * B + 0.5 * C;
E = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * C;
F = 0.4 * A + 0.6 * D;
filldraw(F--D--E--cycle, gray);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--E);
draw(A--D);
label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, NW);
label("$C$", C, NE);
label("$D$", D, SE);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, SW);

label("$8$", (B + E)/2, NW);
label("$8$", (E + C)/2, NE);
label("$4$", (F + D)/2, SW);
label("$4$", (D + C)/2, SE);
[/asy]

Now, we can reconstruct the areas of the other regions.  Since $\triangle EFC$ and $\triangle AFE$ have the same area, $\triangle AFE$ has area 8.  Since $\triangle DFC$ and $\triangle DFB$ have the same area, $\triangle DFB$ has area 8.  Then $\triangle AFD$ has area 4, so $\triangle ABE$ has area 12.  Finally, $\triangle ADC$ has area 24, so $\triangle ABC$ has area $\boxed{48}.$

[asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, F;
A = (0, 4);
B = (-3, 0);
C = (7, 0);
D = 0.5 * B + 0.5 * C;
E = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * C;
F = 0.4 * A + 0.6 * D;
filldraw(F--D--E--cycle, gray);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--E);
draw(A--D);
label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, NW);
label("$C$", C, NE);
label("$D$", D, SE);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, SW);

label("$4$", (A + F)/2, NW);
label("$8$", (B + F)/2, NW);
label("$8$", (E + C)/2, NE);
label("$4$", (F + D)/2, SW);
label("$4$", (D + C)/2, SE);
[/asy]

