Let $x = CG.$  Then $EG = 7 - x,$ and $AG = 2EG,$ so
\[\frac{10}{3} = 2(7 - x).\]Solving, we find $x = \frac{17}{3}.$

By the median formula on triangle $ACF,$
\[BC^2 = 2 \cdot AF^2 + 2 \cdot AC^2 - 4 \cdot FG^2 = 18 + 2 \cdot AC^2 - \frac{100}{9}.\]By the median formula on triangle $ACG,$
\[BC^2 = 2 \cdot AG^2 + 2 \cdot AC^2 - 4 \cdot CG^2 = \frac{200}{9} + 2 \cdot AC^2 - \frac{289}{9}.\]Hence, $18 + 2 \cdot AC^2 - \frac{100}{9} = \frac{200}{9} + 2 \cdot AC^2 - \frac{289}{9},$ so $AC = \frac{17}{3}.$  Then $BC^2 = 49,$ so $BC = \boxed{7}.$

