Let $P'$ be the point on $\overline{OO'}$ such that $PP'$ is perpendicular to $\overline{OO'}.$  Then $OP' = 250 \cos \theta$ and $P'O = 250 \sin \theta,$ where $\theta = \angle PO'O'.$  Then
\[O'P' = OO' - OP' = \frac{2\pi}{5} \cdot 600 - 250 \cos \theta = 240 \pi - 250 \cos \theta.\]Then
\begin{align*}
PQ' &= \sqrt{(O'P')^2 + (P'O)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{(240 \pi - 250 \cos \theta)^2 + (250 \sin \theta)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{240^2 \pi^2 - 2 \cdot 250 \cdot 240 \pi \cos \theta + 250^2}.
\end{align*}Then $PQ = PQ' = \sqrt{240^2 \pi^2 - 2 \cdot 250 \cdot 240 \pi \cos \theta + 250^2}.$

Similarly, if we let $Q'$ be the point on $\overline{OO'}$ such that $QQ'$ is perpendicular to $\overline{OO'},$ then
\[PQ = \sqrt{240^2 \pi^2 + 2 \cdot 250 \cdot 240 \pi \cos \theta + 250^2}.\]To minimize $PQ,$ we have to minimize the expression
\[\sqrt{240^2 \pi^2 - 2 \cdot 250 \cdot 240 \pi \cos \theta + 250^2}.\]The minimum occurs when $\cos \theta$ is maximized, which occurs when $\theta = 0.$  Thus,
\[PQ = \sqrt{240^2 \pi^2 + 250^2} = \boxed{250 \sqrt{6 + 24 \pi^2}}.\]

