Triangle $POD$ is a 45-45-90 triangle, so $DO = DP = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$.  Therefore, the coordinates of $P$ are $\left(-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, -\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\right)$, so
\[\tan (180^\circ + 45^\circ) = \frac{\sin 225^\circ}{\cos 225^\circ} = \frac{-\sqrt{2}/2}{-\sqrt{2}/2} = \boxed{1}.\]

